data.name: helptextLabel.Text
data.value:
Ping Monitor is a Network Monitoring Tool which helps you monitor the status of your network devices by periodically sending Ping requests to them and checking their online status.
To add a new device to the Network Map, right click anywhere in the window and select "Add Device" in the context menu that pops up. You will be prompted to enter information about the device, such as IP address, device name, etc. Once you have finished entering this information, click the "Add" button and the device will appear on the map. Ping Monitor will now automatically send Ping requests to the device and display its online status.
If the "Perform ARP Requests" checkbox is checked, the program will NOT send pings to the entered device. Instead, it will send ARP requests. This allows for monitoring of possible MITM devices disguising themselves as an important network device. However, this only works in the local network, not across the internet.
Once added to the Network Map, you can edit or delete devices by simply right-clicking them and selecting the appropriate option. You can move them around the map by dragging them around while holding the left mouse button as well.
If at least one device has been added to the Network Map, it can be exported as a .pmc (Ping Monitor Configuration) file using the appropriate option in the right-click menu. Once saved, a configuration can be imported using the Import option in the same menu.
